
<%= @post.title %><br>
<%= @post.content %><br>

<ul>
<%= @post.comments.each do |c| %>
    <li><%= c.content %></li>
    <%end%>
</ul>

<ul>
<%= @post.users.each do |u| %>
    <li><%= link_to u.username, user_path(u) %></li>
    <%end%>
</ul>
    
<%= form_for(@post) do |f| %>
    <%= f.fields_for :comments do |c| %>
        <%= f.label :content %>
        <%= f.text_field :content %>
    <%end%>
    <br>
    <%= f.label :title %>
    <%= f.text_field :title %>
    <br>
    <%= f.label :username %>
    <%= f.collection_select :user_ids, User.all, :id, :username %>
    <%= f.fields_for :users, @post.users.new do |u| %>
    <%= u.text_field :username %>
        <%end%>

    <%= f.submit %>
<%end%>

<br>
A list of all the unique users who have commented on the post. 
A user's name should only show up once in this section, even 
if they've commented multiple times.

A form to add a new comment. The form should have a drop-down 
menu to select a user (we'll change this in future lessons to 
automatically associate the comment with a logged-in user). We 
should also be able to create a new user here and automatically 
associate it with the post.